  "original_title": "Opposition must support PM, govt, give them six months to resolve crisis: Minister",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Opposition must support PM, govt, give them six months to resolve crisis: Minister",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Parties represented in Sri Lanka\u2019s parliament must extend support to Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe and the government to bring the country out of the present economic crisis, Agriculture Minister Mahinda Amaraweera said, asking opposition parties to give Wickremesinghe six months.",
        "Speaking at the weekly cabinet press briefing on Tuesday July 05, Amaraweera claimed that the incumbent government is an all-party government as is the current demand. He was responding to a question about a request by the Buddhist clergy and others for an interim government comprising all parties represented in parliament. On Monday, Opposition Leader Sajith Premadasa and former President Maithripala Sirisena held discussions on the same.",
        "\u201cThis is an all party government. Invitations are still open to all parties to join. Prime Minister Wickremesinghe already extended an invitation to other parties when he was appointed,\u201d said Amaraweera.",
        "\u201cBefore we engage in politics, we first need to have a country. Instead of thinking about who will be in power next, all people\u2019s representatives must take up the responsibility of [resolving the crisis].\u201d",
        "The minister said opposition parties must support the government without fighting for power at this juncture.",
        "\u201cGive this prime minister and the government six months,\u201d he said, claiming that he had faith that Wickremesinghe and the government could steer Sri Lanka out of its worst economic crisis since Independence.",
        "\u201cBefore [the current dispensation], there were 13-hour power cuts. Gas will be distributed soon. Fertilizer is being distributed already. Fuel will from next week.",
        "\u201cThere\u2019s a pressing need for everyone to unite without sabotaging this, without trying to use this to their advantage,\u201d he said.",
        "Unprecedented forex shortages in Sri Lanka have led to crippling shortages of essentials including fuel, and public anger is at an all time high with massive protests planned for July 09 demanding the resignation of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa and the government. (Colombo/Jul05/2022)"
      ],
